VDujail (3351\u2032N 4414\u2032E\ufeff / \ufeff33.850N 44.233E\ufeff / 33.850; 44.233, Arabic: \u0627\u0644\u062f\u062c\u064a\u0644; alternate spelling: Ad Dujayl) is a small Shi'a town in the Saladin Province. It is situated about 65 kilometers (40&#160;mi) north of Iraq's capital, Baghdad, and has approximately 10,000 inhabitants. It is the site of the 1982 Dujail Massacre [1] and the 2008 Dujail bombing.\u000a
